   <body>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA"><a name="DUC5b3cee082b3c10058188873ba02d26d2"></a>Steering angle adjustment
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e7391"> </a>Loosen the nuts (2).
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e7393"> </a>Loosen the adjusting dowels (3) on both sides of the bottom yoke.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e7395"> </a>Use a 6 to 6.5&nbsp;mm spacer (A) fitted to the fork sleeve, or use a gauge.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e7397"> </a>Turn the front forks to the right until the spacer (A) is seated against the frame top tube.
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_7_023103369.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e7402"> </a>Turn the adjuster dowel (3) on the opposite side to bring it into contact with the retainer on the steering head.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e7404"> </a>Apply threadlocker to the thread of nut (2).
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e7406"> </a>Hold the dowel (3) firm and tighten the nut (2).
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e7408"> </a>Turn the forks to the opposite side: and repeat the process to adjust the other adjuster dowel and tighten the relative nut.
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_7_023203370.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="Attenzione"><img class="Attenzione" width="28" height="25" style="display: inline; float: none; left: 0.0; text-align: left; top: 0.0;" src="img/warning.jpg">Warning
      </div>
      <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e7413"> </a>Check steering lock correct operation both on the right side and on the left side.
      </div>
      <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e7415"> </a>In case of malfunction, repeat the steering adjustment procedure above until bike track alignment is perfect, i.e. until steering
         lock works correctly.
      </div>
      <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e7417"> </a>After checking this point, make sure that the handlebar turned fully to the left does not interfere with the clutch master
         cylinder filler cap on reservoir, and that - with the handlebar turned fully to the right - the throttle control does not
         interfere with fuel tank.
      </div>
   </body>
